---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InteractiveChecker from '../components/InteractiveChecker.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Phishing Email Checker - Scan Suspicious Emails - TrustChecker"
  description="Validate suspicious emails and subject lines for phishing triggers, credential farming, and payment scams. Protect your bank accounts."
  activePath="/phishing-email-checker"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-10">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-4 select-none">
      <span class="caption-mono text-link font-semibold">EMAIL FORENSICS</span>
      <h1 class="display-lg text-ink font-semibold">Phishing email checker.</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-body max-w-lg">
        Determine if an email is a scam. Paste email text, sender info, or link details below to check for credential theft and bait indicators.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Checker Dashboard -->
    <InteractiveChecker defaultTab="email" />

    <!-- Educational section -->
    <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-10 select-none flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="display-sm text-ink">How to identify phishing emails.</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-xs text-body leading-relaxed">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">1. Check the Sender Header Address</span>
          <p>
            Scammers spoof display names (e.g. showing "Netflix Support" as name, but actual sender address is `billing-updates-netflix@support-verification.top`). Always check the actual domain after the `@` symbol.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">2. High Pressure & Urgency Tactics</span>
          <p>
            Phishing attacks use panic-triggering threats ("Your account will be suspended within 24 hours" or "Suspicious transactions resolved on your credit card") to induce impulsive link clicks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">3. Requesting Gift Cards or Money Transfers</span>
          <p>
            Legitimate companies will never demand billing resolutions using Amazon/iTunes gift cards, crypto deposits, or instant wire transfers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">4. Clumsy Grammar or Generic Greetings</span>
          <p>
            Vague salutations like "Dear Customer" or "Valued Client" suggest automated phishing templates sent to millions of people simultaneously.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
